00:00:19,360 --> 00:00:21,351
(Door opening and footsteps)

2
00:00:21,400 --> 00:00:23,391
(Coughing and chatter)

3
00:00:28,600 --> 00:00:31,398
(Man rustles paper and clears throat)

4
00:00:31,440 --> 00:00:34,193
MAN: This is a poem, that was...

5
00:00:35,880 --> 00:00:38,519
Um,  o it i the ia.

6
00:00:38,920 --> 00:00:40,911
Clears throat) It's for my son.

7
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:44,638
To A Child Dancing In The Wind.

8
00:00:47,160 --> 00:00:49,151
""Dance there upon the shore

9
00:00:50,120 --> 00:00:51,838
What need have you to care

10
00:00:51,880 --> 00:00:53,677
For wind or waters roar?.

11
00:00:53,720 --> 00:00:55,278
Tumble out your hair

12
00:00:56,160 --> 00:00:58,116
That the salt drops have wet

13
00:00:59,880 --> 00:01:01,757
What need have you to dread

14
00:01:01,800 --> 00:01:03,677
The monstrous crying of the wind?. ""

15
00:01:08,560 --> 00:01:10,835
(Laughter)

16
00:01:31,160 --> 00:01:33,151
(Gulls cry)

17
00:01:34,200 --> 00:01:36,191
(Waves lap the shore)

18
00:01:45,320 --> 00:01:47,834
Excuse me. Excuse me. Excuse me.

19
00:02:08,120 --> 00:02:09,473
Excuse me.

20
00:02:10,920 --> 00:02:11,670
James.

21
00:02:11,720 --> 00:02:12,948
James?.

22
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:14,752
James!. James!. Come here.

23
00:02:16,200 --> 00:02:18,236
Stay close, OK?.

24
00:02:18,280 --> 00:02:20,714
Give me your hand, tight. Hold it tight.

25
00:02:31,040 --> 00:02:33,031
Sorry. Sorry.

26
00:02:35,040 --> 00:02:36,678
- Sorry.
- Where are they?.

27
00:02:48,960 --> 00:02:51,713
Listen, Frank,
You look after yourself, all right?.

28
00:02:51,760 --> 00:02:54,149
Angela, this way.

29
00:02:54,200 --> 00:02:55,713
Sorry. Excuse me.

30
00:02:57,240 --> 00:02:59,754
(Cheering and whistling)
- There she goes, boys.

31
00:03:06,240 --> 00:03:08,549
Look at that. Isn't that fantastic?.

32
00:03:13,840 --> 00:03:16,559
- Rob!.
- Mum, there you are.

33
00:03:16,600 --> 00:03:19,160
Hello. I thought I was going to miss it.

34
00:03:21,440 --> 00:03:23,908
- Where's Grandpa?.
- I don't know.

35
00:03:30,120 --> 00:03:32,429
Pappy won't be coming. He's not here.

36
00:03:49,640 --> 00:03:51,232
Come on, Frank.

37
00:03:56,760 --> 00:03:59,274
You're missing it, Frank.

38
00:04:06,360 --> 00:04:09,079
- You coming out?.
- I'll be out in a minute, Danny.

39
00:04:22,080 --> 00:04:25,231
How can they let someone else
build our navy's ships?.

40
00:04:25,280 --> 00:04:27,271
It's just the way it is.

41
00:04:27,320 --> 00:04:29,311
And you...

42
00:04:29,360 --> 00:04:31,476
How can they let you go?.

43
00:04:33,680 --> 00:04:36,240
- You want this?.
- No, thanks.

44
00:04:57,760 --> 00:04:59,239
All right, Gus?.

45
00:04:59,280 --> 00:05:01,077
(Whirring of machinery)

46
00:05:02,280 --> 00:05:05,636
(Siren)
- You all right?.

47
00:05:28,400 --> 00:05:31,039
- Joan Redmond?.
- Yeah, I'm sorry.

48
00:05:31,080 --> 00:05:33,435
Excuse me. I'm sorry.

49
00:05:34,400 --> 00:05:36,595
Excuse me. I'm sorry.

50
00:05:40,880 --> 00:05:42,074
- Sorry.
- Right...

51
00:05:42,120 --> 00:05:45,908
As I was saying, driving a bus
is exactly the same as driving a car,

52
00:05:45,960 --> 00:05:49,748
except for the 50 or so back-seat drivers
sitting behind you.

53
00:05:57,600 --> 00:05:59,591
(Door opens)

54
00:06:08,720 --> 00:06:10,711
Rob brought the boys for your last day.

55
00:06:14,520 --> 00:06:16,511
They were looking for you.

56
00:06:16,560 --> 00:06:19,791
Gus Fuller lost his hand today.

57
00:06:19,840 --> 00:06:21,239
Oh!

58
00:06:22,600 --> 00:06:23,589
How?.

59
00:06:23,640 --> 00:06:26,791
- One of the presses.
- (Gasps)

60
00:06:32,360 --> 00:06:33,793
Will he get more money?.

61
00:06:35,800 --> 00:06:37,791
I watched him do it.

62
00:07:27,320 --> 00:07:29,311
That's you tidy.

63
00:07:36,560 --> 00:07:38,551
See you soon, love.

64
00:08:01,080 --> 00:08:02,593
- Hello.
- Hi.

65
00:08:02,640 --> 00:08:06,872
- JSA, pensions or disability?.
- I'm looking for a job.

66
00:08:06,920 --> 00:08:08,512
First time?.

67
00:08:08,560 --> 00:08:11,597
- Yeah.
- You'll need to speak to someone.

68
00:08:12,560 --> 00:08:13,959
Let's see who's free.

69
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:30,752
Angela.

70
00:08:30,800 --> 00:08:33,792
- All right?.
- OK.

71
00:08:56,360 --> 00:08:59,318
Look, Frank, you don't have to fill it in here.

72
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:01,831
You can do it at home.

73
00:09:16,040 --> 00:09:17,632
(Breathes rapidly)

74
00:09:26,040 --> 00:09:28,031
(Panting)

75
00:09:41,560 --> 00:09:45,519
- Won't be the same at work without Frank.
- You got the boot as well, you dozy pillock!

76
00:09:45,560 --> 00:09:48,597
He might have a heart attack.
That happens, doesn't it?.

77
00:09:48,640 --> 00:09:50,676
Work, Monday.
Redundant, Tuesday.

78
00:09:50,720 --> 00:09:52,836
Heart attack, Wednesday.

79
00:09:52,880 --> 00:09:55,838
Frank will be all right, then. Today's Thursday.

80
00:09:56,600 --> 00:10:00,070
What in the name of total insanity
are you wearing?.

81
00:10:00,120 --> 00:10:03,999
- Och, I had nae clean ones.
- Tell me they're not your mother's.

82
00:10:04,720 --> 00:10:06,676
Don't be daft. They're big Janine's.

83
00:10:06,720 --> 00:10:10,269
- She left them in the pub on Friday.
- Don't let Frank catch you wearing them.

84
00:10:10,320 --> 00:10:13,153
- I knew they'd come in handy.
- For what exactly?.

85
00:10:13,200 --> 00:10:15,111
What if I get run over?.

86
00:10:17,440 --> 00:10:22,195
Frank won't be coming swimming tonight.
I'm glad I got out when I did. It's turned nasty.

87
00:10:22,240 --> 00:10:24,834
Frank could have stayed like I did.
The men respect him.

88
00:10:24,880 --> 00:10:28,668
All he had to do was let them upstairs think
they were running the job.

89
00:10:28,720 --> 00:10:30,836
Man's too pig-headed for his own good.

90
00:10:38,440 --> 00:10:41,318
- Frank, I didn't mean...
- Leave it, Eddie.

91
00:10:48,960 --> 00:10:50,473
See you in the pool, then.

92
00:11:40,440 --> 00:11:41,429
Frank?.

93
00:11:45,520 --> 00:11:47,670
Frank?.

94
00:11:49,160 --> 00:11:50,752
- Frank?.
JOAN: Excuse me.

95
00:11:50,800 --> 00:11:52,472
Frank?.

96
00:11:53,360 --> 00:11:55,715
Frank, where are you going?.

97
00:11:56,560 --> 00:11:58,676
EDDlE: Frank!
JOAN: Oh, my God!

98
00:11:58,720 --> 00:11:59,755
Frank!

99
00:11:59,800 --> 00:12:02,519
Hey, man. Hey!

100
00:12:02,560 --> 00:12:04,152
Get an ambulance, Joan!

101
00:12:04,200 --> 00:12:06,111
Please, no.

102
00:12:06,160 --> 00:12:07,718
You're all right, man.

103
00:12:07,760 --> 00:12:09,751
Get out of my way!

104
00:12:15,520 --> 00:12:17,715
It's OK. He's OK. Dad's fine.

105
00:12:18,440 --> 00:12:21,034
It was a panic attack.
That's what the doctor said.

106
00:12:21,080 --> 00:12:22,513
- What?.
- A panic attack.

107
00:12:22,560 --> 00:12:25,028
Only, don't mention it when he comes out.

108
00:12:25,080 --> 00:12:27,071
OK, let's go.

109
00:12:27,120 --> 00:12:29,236
- Eddie rang me.
- Eddie's got a big mouth.

110
00:12:29,280 --> 00:12:31,475
- He was worried.
- I slipped, OK?.

111
00:12:31,520 --> 00:12:34,557
- Can I get money for a can of Coke?.
- You collapsed.

112
00:12:34,600 --> 00:12:37,717
- Mum says you had a panic attack.
- I slipped and fell. It happens.

113
00:12:37,760 --> 00:12:40,877
- What are you asking me for?.
- Have you got money for a can of Coke?.

114
00:12:40,920 --> 00:12:42,751
No, I don't. Have you got your purse?.

115
00:12:42,800 --> 00:12:45,314
- No, I don't have my purse.
- Ask your dad for the money.

116
00:12:45,360 --> 00:12:47,157
- How do I get out of here?.
- Down there.

117
00:12:47,200 --> 00:12:48,838
- Right, left?.
- That way, Frank.

118
00:12:48,880 --> 00:12:52,077
- Right, I'll find it.
- I'm really sorry, love.

119
00:12:53,200 --> 00:12:55,350
Come on, boys, let's go.

120
00:12:56,400 --> 00:12:59,039
- What is the matter with you?.
- You shouldn't...

121
00:12:59,080 --> 00:13:02,356
- You could have said hello.
- You should not have told him.

122
00:13:08,240 --> 00:13:09,116
(Bell)

123
00:13:09,160 --> 00:13:11,993
- Hands.
(Lift door shuts)

124
00:13:20,840 --> 00:13:23,957
- Is Pappy all right?.
- Of course he is.

125
00:13:29,960 --> 00:13:32,030
Do you like Pappy?.

126
00:13:32,080 --> 00:13:34,275
Pappy and I are just different.

127
00:13:35,720 --> 00:13:37,392
Pappy doesn't like you.

128
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:52,275
Oh, look who it is. Frank's little girl.

129
00:13:52,320 --> 00:13:54,117
(Sniggering)

130
00:13:55,640 --> 00:13:58,871
Are ourfish suppers ready yet, Chinaman?.

131
00:13:58,920 --> 00:14:03,072
Oh, God love us.
He's a real chatterbox tonight, isn't he?.

132
00:14:03,120 --> 00:14:04,394
(Chuckling)

133
00:14:05,480 --> 00:14:07,311
Tell you what. I've changed my mind.

134
00:14:07,360 --> 00:14:09,351
I fancy a curry.

135
00:14:18,720 --> 00:14:20,551
See you Tuesday.

136
00:14:28,560 --> 00:14:30,551
Just a bag of chips, please, Chan.

137
00:14:32,560 --> 00:14:36,030
I heard about your Dad. I'm er...sorry.

138
00:14:46,080 --> 00:14:48,071
OK, Chan?.

139
00:14:48,760 --> 00:14:50,432
Frank, all right?.

140
00:14:51,480 --> 00:14:52,959
Good book?.

141
00:14:54,000 --> 00:14:57,037
It's for my wife. It's about cooking.

142
00:14:59,360 --> 00:15:01,351
What are you looking for?.

143
00:15:03,600 --> 00:15:05,591
I don't know.

144
00:15:07,200 --> 00:15:09,236
But whatever it is, it's not in here.

145
00:15:17,640 --> 00:15:20,313
JOAN: He doesn't know
what to do with himself any more.

146
00:15:20,360 --> 00:15:23,033
More than I can say for you, driving a bus.
Have you told him?.

147
00:15:23,080 --> 00:15:26,117
No. Don't want to give him
anything else to worry about.

148
00:15:26,160 --> 00:15:28,754
He's going to find out sooner or later.

149
00:15:28,800 --> 00:15:31,917
He's shut me out again, Michelle.
Like when Stuart...

150
00:15:31,960 --> 00:15:35,316
It won't last long.
Are things better with him and Rob?.

151
00:15:35,360 --> 00:15:36,679
Not really.

152
00:15:47,200 --> 00:15:48,758
- Good evening.
- Hiya.

153
00:15:48,800 --> 00:15:50,392
- Bag of chips, please.
- OK.

154
00:15:55,360 --> 00:15:58,238
- Is your Dad around?.
- No.

155
00:15:58,960 --> 00:16:00,951
Salt and vinegar?.

156
00:16:01,720 --> 00:16:02,914
Please.

157
00:16:17,800 --> 00:16:19,791
(Laughter on TV)

158
00:16:20,480 --> 00:16:24,109
Oh, hi, Frank. Come on in.
I'm just off to work.

159
00:16:24,960 --> 00:16:26,791
Tom Cruise is in the front room.

160
00:16:26,840 --> 00:16:30,310
Eddie, it's Frank. He's got chips.

161
00:16:37,000 --> 00:16:42,279
TV:..but our industrious little beetle is about
to meet someone altogether more scary...

162
00:16:42,320 --> 00:16:44,311
I've seen this before.

163
00:16:45,520 --> 00:16:51,914
That wee beetle pushes that big ball of shite
for what is the equivalent of six miles for him.

164
00:16:51,960 --> 00:16:54,235
Then just as he gets to where he's going,

165
00:16:55,400 --> 00:16:57,755
another beetle comes...

166
00:16:57,800 --> 00:16:59,870
and steals it from under his nose.

167
00:16:59,920 --> 00:17:02,434
It's what happens. Wait, you'll see.

168
00:17:02,480 --> 00:17:04,675
Six miles.

169
00:17:04,720 --> 00:17:06,711
Poor bastard.

170
00:17:06,760 --> 00:17:09,479
They'll have you shovelling shit, you know that?.

171
00:17:11,880 --> 00:17:13,871
I know.

172
00:17:16,880 --> 00:17:19,633
You still coming on the booze cruise to France?.

173
00:17:19,680 --> 00:17:21,511
It will do us good.

174
00:17:21,560 --> 00:17:23,551
I can see myself on the ship now.

175
00:17:24,600 --> 00:17:27,910
Captain Eddie Fraser, beer in my hand

176
00:17:28,720 --> 00:17:31,154
and the sea air in my lungs.

177
00:17:31,200 --> 00:17:32,758
DANNY: Oh, Eddie!.

178
00:17:32,800 --> 00:17:35,030
That seagull's eating your puke.

179
00:17:36,800 --> 00:17:40,429
He caught it in the air.
That seagull caught it in the air.

180
00:17:40,480 --> 00:17:43,597
Puke again, Eddie. Go on, puke again.

181
00:17:48,240 --> 00:17:49,912
That's brilliant that.

182
00:18:05,720 --> 00:18:07,711
All right?.

183
00:18:09,000 --> 00:18:10,558
Bloody hell.

184
00:18:10,600 --> 00:18:14,434
You can see France already.
Isn't very far, is it?.

185
00:18:14,480 --> 00:18:16,311
Near enough to swim.

186
00:18:16,360 --> 00:18:18,590
I wish I had.

187
00:18:32,560 --> 00:18:33,754
(Laughter)

188
00:18:44,920 --> 00:18:46,478
EDDlE: Frank?.

189
00:18:47,880 --> 00:18:50,030
Frank?.

190
00:18:50,080 --> 00:18:52,071
You all right?.

191
00:18:55,720 --> 00:18:58,075
How mad would you have to be to swim this?.

192
00:18:58,800 --> 00:19:00,279
Totally.

193
00:19:08,080 --> 00:19:11,470
DANNY: How far is it to France?.
EDDlE: We're in France, you dipstick.

194
00:19:12,200 --> 00:19:15,158
DANNY: I know we're in France
but how far is it from Britain?.

195
00:19:15,200 --> 00:19:18,829
NORMAN: 20 miles,
give or take the odd oil tanker.

196
00:19:18,880 --> 00:19:21,030
DANNY: 20 miles, eh?.
How do they measure that?.

197
00:19:21,080 --> 00:19:23,548
MlCHELLE: They look very small from here.

198
00:19:23,600 --> 00:19:27,309
They are very small. It's just
us women like to shrink when we get near them.

199
00:19:27,360 --> 00:19:31,672
You can't just swim across
one of the busiest shipping routes in the world.

200
00:19:31,720 --> 00:19:34,678
Who do you show your passport to?.
Punch and Judy?.

201
00:19:34,720 --> 00:19:38,349
- The deckchair man.
- I was a deckchair man for a day.

202
00:19:38,400 --> 00:19:41,597
- Only a day?.
- It wasn't what I was expecting.

203
00:19:42,760 --> 00:19:46,548
MlCHELLE: Did you tell him yet?.
JOAN: No. God, no.

204
00:19:46,600 --> 00:19:48,591
I will.

205
00:19:48,640 --> 00:19:51,996
He won't like it.
He'll think it's to do with him losing his job.

206
00:19:52,040 --> 00:19:55,953
MlCHELLE: And he'll like it even less
when he finds out the truth.

207
00:19:56,000 --> 00:19:58,753
That it's got absolutely nothing
to do with him at all.

208
00:20:15,800 --> 00:20:19,873
Sorry to pull you back to the yard like this,
Frank. It's a small little matter.

209
00:20:19,920 --> 00:20:23,549
I just need to prove something.
I know you must be busy.

210
00:20:24,880 --> 00:20:26,871
So, you know these guys, Frank?.

211
00:20:28,200 --> 00:20:31,829
- So...
- I've told you...I didn't see anything.

212
00:20:33,720 --> 00:20:36,792
He must have been desperate.
He's going to get nothing.

213
00:20:37,880 --> 00:20:39,871
He used the wrong hand.

214
00:20:42,120 --> 00:20:43,917
He's right-handed.

215
00:20:44,960 --> 00:20:45,631
Duncan.

216
00:20:48,480 --> 00:20:50,516
He crossed hands...

217
00:20:50,560 --> 00:20:52,152
to operate the press.

218
00:20:55,840 --> 00:20:56,829
OK.

219
00:21:00,720 --> 00:21:03,917
You should have been more loyal
to the company, Frank.

220
00:21:04,720 --> 00:21:06,438
You wouldn't know what loyalty is.

221
00:21:07,240 --> 00:21:09,629
Loyalty is a full wage packet
at the end of the week.

222
00:21:10,880 --> 00:21:12,871
Loyalty is being valued.

223
00:21:13,880 --> 00:21:16,155
Being happy with yourself.

224
00:21:17,080 --> 00:21:19,469
Are you happy with yourself, Frank?.

225
00:21:21,600 --> 00:21:23,591
Who do you think you are?.

226
00:21:25,080 --> 00:21:28,755
You seriously think you can intimidate people
into being loyal to you?.

227
00:21:30,720 --> 00:21:34,269
There's not a man in this yard
would piss on you if you were on fire.

228
00:21:41,840 --> 00:21:43,353
Hi, Frank.

229
00:21:43,400 --> 00:21:45,197
Cannae keep away, eh?.

230
00:22:51,680 --> 00:22:54,319
- I knocked a vase over.
- Which one?.

231
00:22:54,360 --> 00:22:57,591
- The one with the crack in it?.
- No, the other one.

232
00:22:59,920 --> 00:23:01,911
Will it fix?.

233
00:23:07,160 --> 00:23:09,151
I need to go and get changed.

234
00:23:09,200 --> 00:23:11,191
(Squelches)

235
00:23:15,560 --> 00:23:18,438
So what if you swam the Clyde?.
It doesn't prove anything.

236
00:23:18,480 --> 00:23:20,789
The Channel's a completely different thing.

237
00:23:20,840 --> 00:23:23,400
- Do you think you could, then, Frank?.
- I know I could.

238
00:23:23,440 --> 00:23:26,557
EDDlE: Look...you got made redundant.

239
00:23:26,600 --> 00:23:29,273
You should just face up to it like everyone else.

240
00:23:43,560 --> 00:23:45,551
Face up to it?.

241
00:23:50,440 --> 00:23:52,431
Like you did, Eddie?.

242
00:24:12,320 --> 00:24:15,118
- That's a lot of reading.
- It's a lot of swimming.

243
00:24:15,800 --> 00:24:19,713
- You think I'm wasting my time?.
- A gem cannot be polished without friction,

244
00:24:19,760 --> 00:24:22,035
nor a man perfected without trials.

245
00:24:24,560 --> 00:24:28,599
- Is that a yes or a no?.
- When do we start?.

246
00:24:47,920 --> 00:24:50,673
Hey, hey, hey.
What have we forgotten?.

247
00:24:55,360 --> 00:24:57,351
What's this?.

248
00:24:58,280 --> 00:25:00,840
You know we're not allowed. In you go.

249
00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:03,592
I'll see you at 3:30.

250
00:25:03,640 --> 00:25:05,471
- Bye!.
- Bye!

251
00:25:18,040 --> 00:25:19,632
- All right, son.
- Dad.

252
00:25:20,880 --> 00:25:22,108
OK?.

253
00:25:23,960 --> 00:25:25,359
You?.

