Right, OK.

496
00:44:41,960 --> 00:44:46,590
Don't do anything stupid.
If you get into trouble, go to the boat. Yeah?.

497
00:44:46,640 --> 00:44:49,598
All right. Now remember, we're not superheroes.

498
00:44:49,640 --> 00:44:51,756
- I hear you. I'm good.
- OK, let's go.

499
00:44:51,800 --> 00:44:54,109
What's that?.

500
00:44:54,160 --> 00:44:55,957
Jellyfish.

501
00:44:56,640 --> 00:44:58,312
They're fine. They're fine.

502
00:45:01,400 --> 00:45:03,709
Come on!

503
00:45:06,720 --> 00:45:08,711
- It's colder than last time.
- Slow down.

504
00:45:08,760 --> 00:45:11,991
DANNY: Come on, here we go.
FRANK: Right, hey, Danny.

505
00:45:12,040 --> 00:45:14,031
- Watch this.
- Pace yourself.

506
00:45:37,840 --> 00:45:40,400
TAPE: You are king of the jungle.

507
00:45:42,000 --> 00:45:43,991
I am a lion.

508
00:45:45,160 --> 00:45:47,230
Now repeat after me...

509
00:45:54,640 --> 00:45:56,631
(Gasping)

510
00:46:02,040 --> 00:46:04,031
Right, there you go, Frank.

511
00:46:05,960 --> 00:46:08,554
Why can't they just hold onto the boat and get it?.

512
00:46:08,600 --> 00:46:12,752
Frank wants to do it right.
If they touch the boat, the swim won't count.

513
00:46:29,520 --> 00:46:32,512
Now repeat after me,
you are not a man, you are a wolf.

514
00:46:32,560 --> 00:46:35,279
(Tape on fast rewind)

515
00:46:36,160 --> 00:46:38,071
(Car horn)

516
00:46:43,560 --> 00:46:47,348
- Eddie! He's got cramp.
- Start the boat, Chan. Start the boat.

517
00:46:47,400 --> 00:46:50,278
Danny! Danny, hold on!

518
00:46:50,320 --> 00:46:51,958
- Danny!
- Hold on, Danny!

519
00:46:52,000 --> 00:46:53,877
(Engine won't start)

520
00:46:55,560 --> 00:46:57,312
It won't start.

521
00:47:05,160 --> 00:47:08,072
It's OK. Calm down. Take it easy.

522
00:47:37,600 --> 00:47:40,239
- What did the doctor say?.
- It's fine.

523
00:47:40,280 --> 00:47:43,477
The doctor says he's going to be all right,
no thanks to you.

524
00:47:43,520 --> 00:47:45,715
He looks to you like a dad.

525
00:47:45,760 --> 00:47:47,512
You should have stopped him.

526
00:47:48,760 --> 00:47:52,389
- It wasn't Frank's fault, Ma.
- I will not have him go in the water again.

527
00:47:52,440 --> 00:47:54,078
Ma, it was my own fault.

528
00:48:00,080 --> 00:48:02,071
I just wanted to be the man for once.

529
00:48:04,200 --> 00:48:07,397
Olympic superstar, Nike sponsorship.

530
00:48:07,440 --> 00:48:09,670
Just be the man, you know?.

531
00:48:11,920 --> 00:48:13,911
Like you.

532
00:48:17,720 --> 00:48:19,790
I didn't want you to be disappointed.

533
00:48:20,800 --> 00:48:23,917
I was when I found out
it was Eddie that gave me the kiss of life.

534
00:48:28,000 --> 00:48:30,992
- Are you going training now?.
- Mm.

535
00:48:31,040 --> 00:48:33,270
Put some down for me, will you?.

536
00:48:34,400 --> 00:48:37,790
He can help out. On the boat or something.

537
00:48:38,640 --> 00:48:41,677
But he wears a lifejacket
if he's anywhere near you.

538
00:48:45,800 --> 00:48:49,076
- So his mother's not too happy, then?.
- I should have stopped him.

539
00:48:49,120 --> 00:48:51,429
Remember you stopped Rob swimming in here?.

540
00:48:51,480 --> 00:48:52,959
Yeah, he was seven.

541
00:48:53,000 --> 00:48:56,356
He cursed like mad when I pulled him out
because his mates were watching.

542
00:48:56,400 --> 00:48:58,231
Jumped right back in again.

543
00:48:58,280 --> 00:49:01,317
Ah, you know,
if I had disobeyed my father at that age,

544
00:49:01,360 --> 00:49:03,351
he'd have beat the hell out of me.

545
00:49:04,280 --> 00:49:06,271
But I loved him.

546
00:49:07,560 --> 00:49:09,198
I've never hit Rob.

547
00:49:09,240 --> 00:49:10,958
Ever. Not once.

548
00:49:12,600 --> 00:49:15,398
We never can find two words
to say to each other.

549
00:49:18,680 --> 00:49:20,750
Seems like everything's backwards.

550
00:49:22,680 --> 00:49:24,033
FRANK: That's us.

551
00:49:24,080 --> 00:49:27,993
CHAN: Frank, you need to build up
your stamina so we need to go for a big one.

552
00:49:28,040 --> 00:49:30,508
CHAN: 1 5 miles, OK?.
FRANK: OK.

553
00:49:30,560 --> 00:49:34,348
CHAN: Have you been for a medical.
FRANK: Yeah, I got the all-clear.

554
00:49:35,120 --> 00:49:37,873
Why don't we just take a chance
and go down to Dover?.

555
00:49:37,920 --> 00:49:40,229
It's a long way to go if we don't find somebody.

556
00:49:40,280 --> 00:49:43,989
You said yourself,
if we don't find a pilot, you can't swim.

557
00:49:44,040 --> 00:49:46,793
OK. OK. I'll go there later this week.

558
00:49:46,840 --> 00:49:49,877
I'll come for the ride.
Get a saver, should be cheap enough.

559
00:49:49,920 --> 00:49:54,311
Take Danny, too.
Make sure he brings his water wings this time.

560
00:50:03,960 --> 00:50:05,598
It said "apply thickly".

561
00:50:06,800 --> 00:50:08,791
EDDlE: Maybe we overdid it.

562
00:50:22,240 --> 00:50:24,231
- I'm sorry.
- Oh!

563
00:50:24,280 --> 00:50:25,918
Was it the lorry?.

564
00:50:25,960 --> 00:50:28,269
But he swerved first. Lunatic!

565
00:50:28,320 --> 00:50:33,394
Mrs Redmond, you need to be more...
I'll let you go one more time.

566
00:50:41,920 --> 00:50:43,194
There.

567
00:50:43,880 --> 00:50:47,634
Right, I've just had a word with the barmaid.

568
00:50:47,680 --> 00:50:50,513
Apparently there is a guy that can do it.

569
00:50:50,560 --> 00:50:52,949
Goes by the name of Mad Bob.

570
00:50:53,000 --> 00:50:54,353
Mad Bob?.

571
00:50:55,480 --> 00:50:57,436
He doesn't sound normal.

572
00:50:57,480 --> 00:51:00,278
He sounds frigging nuts. Is he here?.

573
00:51:00,320 --> 00:51:02,117
You looking for a boat?.

574
00:51:03,000 --> 00:51:06,390
- We might be.
- Either you are or you're not.

575
00:51:08,680 --> 00:51:09,669
We are.

576
00:51:09,720 --> 00:51:12,837
- So it's you that's going to be swimming?.
- Mm-hm.

577
00:51:19,840 --> 00:51:23,515
If you can't beat me,
you ain't the man to do the swim.

578
00:51:24,240 --> 00:51:26,231
And I ain't the man to take you.

579
00:51:29,080 --> 00:51:31,150
I take it you're Mad Bob?.

580
00:51:40,120 --> 00:51:41,439
We go on three.

581
00:51:46,240 --> 00:51:47,229
One...

582
00:51:48,400 --> 00:51:50,118
..two...

583
00:51:51,000 --> 00:51:51,671
three!

584
00:51:52,640 --> 00:51:55,029
BOB: 850 the crossing. 200 deposit.

585
00:51:55,080 --> 00:51:56,752
No refunds.

586
00:51:56,800 --> 00:51:59,155
But we get to see your boat?.

587
00:51:59,200 --> 00:52:00,428
What for?.

588
00:52:00,480 --> 00:52:02,869
We get to see the boat.

589
00:52:02,920 --> 00:52:05,150
Righty-ho, you get to see the boat.

590
00:52:07,480 --> 00:52:09,277
Shark.

591
00:52:09,320 --> 00:52:10,673
35-footer.

592
00:52:16,800 --> 00:52:19,633
Fell off my bike. Two-wheeler.

593
00:52:20,360 --> 00:52:22,032
FRANK: Let's go.

594
00:52:24,320 --> 00:52:26,311
BOB: There she is.

595
00:52:28,680 --> 00:52:30,238
Is this yours?.

596
00:52:32,920 --> 00:52:34,672
FRANK: It's all right.

597
00:52:35,360 --> 00:52:36,839
It's good.

598
00:52:36,880 --> 00:52:39,269
Yeah, very nice.

599
00:52:40,240 --> 00:52:42,629
CHAN: There you go, fellas.
FRANK: What date is it?.

600
00:52:42,680 --> 00:52:44,910
EDDlE: 22nd June.
CHAN: Aye, it's the 22nd.

601
00:52:44,960 --> 00:52:48,748
NORMAN: Hang on. Is that a two or a five?.
- You sure?.

602
00:52:48,800 --> 00:52:50,791
Yeah, it's the 22nd.

603
00:52:54,000 --> 00:52:56,309
ROB: One...two...three!

604
00:52:58,360 --> 00:52:59,952
(Cheering)

605
00:53:00,000 --> 00:53:01,956
Forthey are jolly good fellows

606
00:53:02,000 --> 00:53:04,389
For they are jolly good fellows

607
00:53:04,800 --> 00:53:07,553
For they are jolly good fellows

608
00:53:07,600 --> 00:53:09,591
And so say all of us

609
00:53:10,040 --> 00:53:11,439
And so say all of us

610
00:53:11,480 --> 00:53:13,675
- Where were you?.
- Sorry, I got held up.

611
00:53:13,720 --> 00:53:16,109
- I'll get you some food.
- No, it's fine, I've...

612
00:53:16,160 --> 00:53:18,151
And a nice big piece of cake.

613
00:53:21,360 --> 00:53:23,749
- Were you waiting for me?.
- They were.

614
00:53:23,800 --> 00:53:26,872
It's fine. It worked out better.
Come on, let's go crazy.

615
00:53:26,920 --> 00:53:28,911
(Shrieking)

616
00:53:34,280 --> 00:53:35,679
Hey!

617
00:53:37,240 --> 00:53:38,593
Here.

618
00:53:38,640 --> 00:53:40,676
So what did you get them?.

619
00:53:40,720 --> 00:53:44,599
The kids?. Since when did I do the shopping?.
Your mother likes to get those things.

620
00:53:46,000 --> 00:53:48,468
You got them those racetracks.

621
00:53:48,520 --> 00:53:50,909
Mum still does that thing
where she signs the card

622
00:53:50,960 --> 00:53:53,633
and makes it look like you've signed it, too.

623
00:53:57,720 --> 00:53:59,392
How's the swimming coming on?.

624
00:53:59,440 --> 00:54:02,273
I heard you are going to swim
the English Channel.

625
00:54:07,800 --> 00:54:10,678
- I didn't tell her.
- You were right not to.

626
00:54:10,720 --> 00:54:12,392
- Why?.
- Because you heard wrong.

627
00:54:13,600 --> 00:54:16,990
I heard that Danny parked Merv's boat
halfway up the beach

628
00:54:17,040 --> 00:54:19,952
and that you are planning
to swim the Channel this summer.

629
00:54:20,000 --> 00:54:22,195
Danny gets carried away.

630
00:54:28,320 --> 00:54:30,629
- Saw you down the library.
- I like reading.

631
00:54:30,680 --> 00:54:32,989
- Saw you down the pool.
- I like swimming.

632
00:54:33,800 --> 00:54:34,630
What?.

633
00:54:36,720 --> 00:54:39,109
I'm going to get some jelly
before it's all gone.

634
00:54:47,360 --> 00:54:49,635
You can have another go, can't you?.

635
00:54:49,680 --> 00:54:52,240
I just can't seem to concentrate lately.

636
00:54:52,280 --> 00:54:56,398
- You told him at last, then?.
- No, it's not that. It's...something else.

637
00:54:58,160 --> 00:55:00,151
I think he might be having an affair.

638
00:55:04,080 --> 00:55:05,672
But he's acting so odd.

639
00:55:05,720 --> 00:55:08,871
- I'm sorry, that's just daft. I mean...
- Well, there's Vera.

640
00:55:08,920 --> 00:55:10,319
(Michelle laughs)

641
00:55:10,360 --> 00:55:12,920
It's not funny.
She rang last week and...

642
00:55:12,960 --> 00:55:15,713
It's probably just got something
to do with the boat.

643
00:55:15,760 --> 00:55:18,115
- What boat?.
- The boat.

644
00:55:18,160 --> 00:55:21,391
The lads are borrowing a boat
to help Frank swim the Channel.

645
00:55:22,320 --> 00:55:23,719
What channel?.

646
00:55:25,040 --> 00:55:26,996
Thank you.

647
00:55:53,680 --> 00:55:55,716
- Nice.
- Mm.

648
00:55:59,320 --> 00:56:01,629
You know we were talking about buying a car?.

649
00:56:02,600 --> 00:56:05,433
Hm, I fixed the wing mirror back on.

650
00:56:06,120 --> 00:56:09,715
Well, Michelle says
Arthur Hall is selling his Metro. It's red.

651
00:56:10,760 --> 00:56:13,593
- Thought we said a new car could wait?.
- No, we didn't. You did.

652
00:56:15,600 --> 00:56:18,239
Well, we have to be careful
with the money from now on.

653
00:56:18,280 --> 00:56:21,317
Michelle says the insides are just like new.

654
00:56:23,920 --> 00:56:28,311
She also says you've been borrowing Merv's
boat to help you train to swim the Channel.

655
00:56:28,360 --> 00:56:32,876
The English Channel. And I was wondering
when you were thinking about telling me.

656
00:56:38,120 --> 00:56:41,351
I was also wondering how it is
we can't afford a new car

657
00:56:41,400 --> 00:56:45,393
but you can afford to pay for a boat
to show you the way to bloody France.

658
00:56:48,320 --> 00:56:52,791
I'd be worried about you trying to swim
all that way, Frank, if I wasn 't so angry.

659
00:56:56,800 --> 00:57:01,396
I've never asked you for anything, Frank.
But honesty was something I took for granted.

660
00:57:51,680 --> 00:57:54,353
Well, look who it is - the three wise monkeys.

661
00:57:54,400 --> 00:57:58,518
Rob, your dad's got a few more lengths to do.
Why don't we wait for him outside?.

662
00:57:58,560 --> 00:58:01,916
I know about his little secret.
I just want to talk to him, all right?.

663
00:58:01,960 --> 00:58:02,949
- Come on.
- Eddie...

664
00:58:03,000 --> 00:58:03,989
Hey!

665
00:58:10,280 --> 00:58:12,271
You're a liar, Dad.

666
00:58:13,320 --> 00:58:16,153
You lied to me about swimming the Channel.

667
00:58:18,920 --> 00:58:21,150
- Maybe I did.
- Why?.

668
00:58:24,480 --> 00:58:27,074
- Is it because I don't have a job?.
- It's not about you.

669
00:58:27,120 --> 00:58:30,874
Because I look after the twins?.
I'm not ashamed of that, Dad.

670
00:58:30,920 --> 00:58:33,275
I'm not ashamed like you think I should be.

671
00:58:33,320 --> 00:58:35,754
Good. You're not ashamed.

672
00:58:35,800 --> 00:58:37,791
No, but you are.

673
00:58:39,840 --> 00:58:41,831
You're the one who's ashamed!

674
00:58:43,240 --> 00:58:45,993
- I'm not listening to this.
- Why?. What are you afraid of?.

675
00:58:46,040 --> 00:58:48,634
Afraid I'll drown?. Look at me, I'm drowning.

676
00:58:55,000 --> 00:58:56,513
36 years.

677
00:58:56,920 --> 00:58:58,831
36 years.

678
00:58:58,880 --> 00:59:01,440
1 2 hours a day, five days a week.

679
00:59:01,480 --> 00:59:05,712
Now you tell me,
when was I supposed to go shopping?.

680
00:59:13,760 --> 00:59:15,751
(Coughs)

681
00:59:44,960 --> 00:59:47,155
He'll be OK. Just needs time to cool off.

682
00:59:47,840 --> 00:59:50,115
We need to make sure you keep up the times.

683
00:59:50,160 --> 00:59:52,310
- No.
- What?.

684
00:59:52,360 --> 00:59:53,349
No.

685
01:00:01,920 --> 01:00:03,672
- I can't do it.
EDDlE: But, Frank...

686
01:00:03,720 --> 01:00:05,517
I can't do it.

687
01:00:06,560 --> 01:00:09,233
FRANK: He's right.
- Come on, Frank. Come on.

688
01:00:09,280 --> 01:00:11,475
I'm not going to be swimming.

689
01:00:33,240 --> 01:00:35,231
(Turns engine off)

690
01:00:36,200 --> 01:00:38,395
Your father didn't mean to hurt you.

691
01:00:42,760 --> 01:00:44,751
I was married once.

692
01:00:48,120 --> 01:00:50,429
Her name was Bridget.

693
01:00:50,480 --> 01:00:52,789
She left me for a jam salesman.

694
01:00:54,440 --> 01:00:56,954
She never even liked jam.

695
01:01:00,800 --> 01:01:03,189
I didn't bother with women again after that.

696
01:01:03,240 --> 01:01:05,913
I was too scared
the same thing would happen all over.

697
01:01:07,160 --> 01:01:10,277
If anyone tried to get close,
I just pushed them away.

698
01:01:14,320 --> 01:01:17,790
Your father did the same thing with you
after the accident.

699
01:01:17,840 --> 01:01:19,353
Pushed you away.

700
01:01:21,080 --> 01:01:22,957
He blames me.

701
01:01:24,040 --> 01:01:26,076
No, he doesn't.

702
01:01:26,120 --> 01:01:28,634
He blames himself. Always has.

703
01:01:33,400 --> 01:01:36,472
Now you're soaking the seat
and it's leather. It'll stain.

704
01:02:25,640 --> 01:02:27,358
All that way, Frank.

705
01:02:36,560 --> 01:02:38,516
I thought we were too old for secrets.

706
01:02:42,880 --> 01:02:45,189
Like learning how to drive a bus?.

707
01:02:56,840 --> 01:02:59,434
There was an ad in the paper.

708
01:03:00,880 --> 01:03:02,871
I failed twice.

709
01:03:04,720 --> 01:03:07,757
But I'm going to take it again.
I'm not giving up.

710
01:03:36,520 --> 01:03:38,511
Let's just play when it smashes.

711
01:03:39,400 --> 01:03:42,278
All right, you ready?.
You take that one, all right?.

712
01:03:53,960 --> 01:03:56,474
ANGELA: We're not catching the train, James.

713
01:03:56,520 --> 01:03:59,717
There's no point in racing,
I've got the keys, remember.

714
01:04:04,600 --> 01:04:06,989
- (Whispers) Pappy?.
- Sh!

715
01:04:08,600 --> 01:04:11,478
- Are you playing a game?.
- Yeah.

716
01:04:11,520 --> 01:04:14,830
ANGELA: Don't make me come back out.
- You better go inside.

717
01:04:19,320 --> 01:04:21,675
- Is it a secret?.
- Yeah.

718
01:04:21,720 --> 01:04:23,676
Like Daddy's wee brother?.

719
01:04:25,240 --> 01:04:28,994
He says we mustn't talk about him.
That it makes you sad.

720
01:04:29,680 --> 01:04:31,557
Does it make you sad?.

721
01:04:32,600 --> 01:04:34,636
Sometimes.

722
01:04:36,560 --> 01:04:38,835
- I won't tell.
- Good boy.

723
01:04:42,920 --> 01:04:44,831
Are you going to swim the Channel?.

724
01:04:46,560 --> 01:04:49,074
I don't know. What do you think?.

725
01:04:49,120 --> 01:04:51,190
Dad says it's too dangerous.

726
01:04:54,560 --> 01:04:56,596
What is the Channel?.

727
01:04:56,640 --> 01:05:00,599
It's the sea between England and France.

728
01:05:02,600 --> 01:05:04,750
Are there any...sharks?.

729
01:05:04,800 --> 01:05:06,631
No sharks.

730
01:05:06,680 --> 01:05:09,638
- Crocodiles?.
- Mm-mn.

731
01:05:09,680 --> 01:05:11,830
- Piranhas?.
- Bananas?.

732
01:05:11,880 --> 01:05:15,111
- Piranhas?.
- Piranhas!

733
01:05:15,160 --> 01:05:17,276
No, no piranhas.

734
01:05:17,320 --> 01:05:19,834
It doesn't sound too dangerous to me, then.

735
01:05:19,880 --> 01:05:21,871
ANGELA: I'll count to five.

736
01:05:32,280 --> 01:05:34,475
I can swim like a fish.

737
01:05:44,640 --> 01:05:47,712
ANGELA: Are you stopping out here all day
or are you coming in?.

738
01:06:21,000 --> 01:06:23,594
Hey, big man, you not swimming?.

739
01:06:48,400 --> 01:06:49,389
Yes!

740
01:06:54,240 --> 01:06:56,834
That's £5 you owe me. I told you he'd be here.

741
01:07:02,920 --> 01:07:04,592
We're the delegation.

742
01:07:05,800 --> 01:07:07,756
A delegation?.

743
01:07:07,800 --> 01:07:11,679
- It's a kind of a gang.
- Thanks for that, Danny.

744
01:07:14,840 --> 01:07:16,990
Does the delegation have a proposal?.

745
01:07:17,040 --> 01:07:18,917
EDDlE: Yeah.

746
01:07:18,960 --> 01:07:20,791
We think you're wrong to give up.

747
01:07:20,840 --> 01:07:22,831
Now we've come this far.

748
01:07:24,160 --> 01:07:27,596
- We also think you're a big daft bollocks...
- See him?.

749
01:07:27,640 --> 01:07:29,517
See that little laddie with red hair?.

750
01:07:31,880 --> 01:07:35,429
It takes everything out of him
just to swim one width. Just one.

751
01:07:37,240 --> 01:07:40,789
He won't take any help and he never gives up.

752
01:07:41,800 --> 01:07:43,119
Ever.

753
01:07:47,840 --> 01:07:50,593
- And when he gets to the other side...
- Yes!

754
01:07:54,200 --> 01:07:56,191
I'm not giving up.

755
01:08:15,800 --> 01:08:17,552
That toilet needs cleaning again.

756
01:08:23,360 --> 01:08:24,759
Do it yourself.

757
01:08:38,160 --> 01:08:40,037
He's on his knees and she's...

758
01:08:40,080 --> 01:08:42,071
Take it steady.

759
01:08:42,760 --> 01:08:45,069
All right, ladies?. Pam.

760
01:08:45,120 --> 01:08:47,270
- Oh, my God!
- All right, love?.

761
01:08:48,240 --> 01:08:50,993
- You nearly finished?.
- Uh-huh.

762
01:08:51,040 --> 01:08:53,031
Only I thought we might go out.

763
01:08:54,280 --> 01:08:55,998
You mean together?.

764
01:09:01,160 --> 01:09:04,675
Oh, aye. You and me. Me and you.

765
01:09:11,600 --> 01:09:12,794
Excuse me.

766
01:09:14,040 --> 01:09:15,837
Please don't drop the bags.

767
01:09:15,880 --> 01:09:17,154
They split.

768
01:09:18,080 --> 01:09:19,479
Oh, aye?.

769
01:09:20,680 --> 01:09:22,352
Sorry, pal.

770
01:09:28,000 --> 01:09:31,356
- See you Wednesday.
- See you Wednesday.

771
01:09:44,080 --> 01:09:45,399
I nearly drowned.

772
01:09:45,440 --> 01:09:47,829
- We heard.
- In the sea.

773
01:09:47,880 --> 01:09:51,759
- What were you doing in the sea?.
- I don't know.

774
01:09:51,800 --> 01:09:53,438
Do you want to go out with me?.

775
01:09:56,160 --> 01:09:57,513
Yeah!

776
01:09:57,560 --> 01:09:59,516
Good.

777
01:09:59,560 --> 01:10:01,152
That's good.

778
01:10:03,080 --> 01:10:04,991
Happy days.

779
01:10:15,760 --> 01:10:17,512
(Shipping forecast on radio)

780
01:10:21,280 --> 01:10:23,555
You smell of chlorine.

781
01:10:23,600 --> 01:10:26,068
Like Dad when he was laid out.

782
01:10:29,480 --> 01:10:32,119
He used to smell of oil and Woodbines.

783
01:10:35,800 --> 01:10:37,791
I was 1 6.

784
01:10:39,200 --> 01:10:41,509
You came round to talk to Dad about something.

785
01:10:42,920 --> 01:10:45,275
I couldn't believe how handsome you were.

786
01:10:54,720 --> 01:10:56,915
I'm learning to drive a bus.

787
01:10:57,600 --> 01:11:00,717
And then, if I pass, I'm going to drive a bus.

788
01:11:01,760 --> 01:11:04,115
It'll be my job, a proper job.

789
01:11:05,640 --> 01:11:07,631
Driving a bus.

790
01:11:10,040 --> 01:11:12,031
I'm going up.

791
01:11:13,000 --> 01:11:16,037
So should you. You have a big day tomorrow.

792
01:11:54,240 --> 01:11:56,595
Thanks for the sandwiches.

793
01:11:57,280 --> 01:11:58,872
Good luck.

794
01:11:58,920 --> 01:12:03,675
That...time when I came to see your father...

795
01:12:04,480 --> 01:12:05,754
I didn't.

796
01:12:07,720 --> 01:12:09,517
I came to see you.

797
01:12:17,040 --> 01:12:19,156
DANNY: I spy with my little eye...

798
01:12:19,200 --> 01:12:21,953
- You'll never get this. A.
FRANK: Air freshener.

799
01:12:22,000 --> 01:12:23,399
EDDlE: Ambulance.
- No.

800
01:12:23,440 --> 01:12:25,556
- You might get it, Norman.
NORMAN: Why?.

801
01:12:25,600 --> 01:12:28,558
Because you're nearer it.
You could say you're on it.

802
01:12:28,600 --> 01:12:30,352
- I'm on it?.
- Kind of.

803
01:12:30,400 --> 01:12:31,753
EDDlE: Arse.
- No.

804
01:12:31,800 --> 01:12:34,268
You'd have that as well.
Unless it was Norman's arse.

805
01:12:34,320 --> 01:12:37,437
NORMAN: Leave my arse out of this.
DANNY: And that would be N-A.

806
01:13:11,240 --> 01:13:13,231
(Gulls cry)

807
01:13:22,840 --> 01:13:25,434
- You OK with heights?.
- Yeah.

808
01:13:26,800 --> 01:13:29,030
- You?.
- Oh, yeah.

809
01:13:29,080 --> 01:13:31,071
- You sure?.
- Mm-hm.

810
01:13:34,080 --> 01:13:37,709
FRANK: I was thinking about Joan.
I should have told her.

811
01:13:39,840 --> 01:13:41,831
Don't know what I was hiding.

812
01:13:43,920 --> 01:13:47,595
- Maybe we should leave him alone.
- Why?. We should be there for him.

813
01:13:47,640 --> 01:13:51,349
- What if he doesn't want us there?.
- Oh, you're as pig-headed as your father.

814
01:13:51,400 --> 01:13:55,234
Of course he wants us there.
He just doesn't know how to ask.

815
01:13:55,280 --> 01:13:58,511
- But he's not going to achieve anything by it.
- How do you know?.

816
01:13:58,560 --> 01:14:02,439
Because he's not going to bring Stuart back
by swimming the Channel.

817
01:14:04,320 --> 01:14:06,515
Oh, Rob.

818
01:14:06,560 --> 01:14:09,438
It's not Stuart he wants back.

819
01:14:13,520 --> 01:14:14,919
I'm away.

820
01:14:21,280 --> 01:14:24,590
- Mum, thanks for the toys.
- It's OK.

821
01:14:27,360 --> 01:14:29,351
What toys?.

822
01:14:36,000 --> 01:14:37,513
(Fart)

823
01:14:37,560 --> 01:14:40,757
DANNY: Better out than in, right?.
EDDlE: For God's sake!

824
01:14:42,000 --> 01:14:45,117
NORMAN: One more of them
and you're sleeping in the car.

825
01:14:45,160 --> 01:14:47,071
(Sniggering)

826
01:14:47,120 --> 01:14:50,715
FRANK: I knew a guy once
could fart in German.

827
01:14:50,760 --> 01:14:52,751
(Laughter)

828
01:15:04,040 --> 01:15:05,917
You took your time.

829
01:15:06,640 --> 01:15:08,631
I'm sitting in the front.

830
01:15:14,120 --> 01:15:16,315
The observer fellow seems all right.

831
01:15:23,600 --> 01:15:25,955
Right, it's five o'clock. Let's get cracking.

832
01:15:26,000 --> 01:15:29,595
OK, don't forget, don't touch the boat
or anyone on it once you get going

833
01:15:29,640 --> 01:15:31,596
or it will invalidate your swim.

834
01:15:31,640 --> 01:15:33,392
When you get to France, get on dry land,

835
01:15:33,440 --> 01:15:35,715
pick up a stone and bring it back to the boat.

836
01:15:35,760 --> 01:15:37,512
OK.

837
01:15:37,560 --> 01:15:40,028
- Good luck.
- Thank you. Thank you.

838
01:15:41,960 --> 01:15:42,949
Well, go.

839
01:15:43,000 --> 01:15:44,956
- Good luck, mate.
- Good luck, Frank.

840
01:15:45,000 --> 01:15:47,116
Thanks, lads.

841
01:15:47,160 --> 01:15:48,354
Right.

842
01:15:52,360 --> 01:15:53,634
See yous.

843
01:15:53,680 --> 01:15:57,434
- You're not joining us?.
- No, I don't float very well.

844
01:15:57,480 --> 01:15:59,516
Me, neither.

845
01:16:02,280 --> 01:16:03,269
OK.

846
01:16:11,240 --> 01:16:13,231
(Boat's engine starts up)

847
01:17:04,320 --> 01:17:06,629
Come on, Frank.

848
01:17:06,680 --> 01:17:08,477
That's the way.

849
01:17:54,160 --> 01:17:56,628
Ah, we'll be there in no time, Frank.

850
01:17:58,320 --> 01:18:00,311
It's a nice rhythm, that.

851
01:18:01,840 --> 01:18:04,752
One, two, three, four...

852
01:18:06,000 --> 01:18:09,754
I'm all right, Frank. I'm all right. Carry on.

853
01:18:13,200 --> 01:18:17,318
- You passed, didn't you?.
- I thought you'd never ask.

854
01:18:17,360 --> 01:18:20,432
Well done, Mum.
Congratulations, that's brilliant!

855
01:18:20,480 --> 01:18:22,835
JOAN: I think we should celebrate
with a gum drop.

856
01:18:41,520 --> 01:18:44,273
- The fumes are killing me.
- I can't help that.

857
01:18:46,360 --> 01:18:48,920
I'm keeping this close to keep you on course.

858
01:18:50,520 --> 01:18:52,636
FRANK: I can't breathe.

859
01:18:52,680 --> 01:18:55,353
- I'll go ahead.
- Well, what bloody use will I be then?.

860
01:18:57,840 --> 01:19:00,638
Stupid bastard. Bloody fool.

861
01:19:08,280 --> 01:19:10,840
TAPE: I am confident.

862
01:19:10,880 --> 01:19:14,190
- I am confident.
- I am a lion.

863
01:19:14,240 --> 01:19:16,629
I am a lion.
I'm not a timorous beastie.

864
01:19:16,680 --> 01:19:18,830
I am a lion.

865
01:19:37,480 --> 01:19:39,710
EDDlE: He's doing great.
- No, he's not.

866
01:19:39,760 --> 01:19:42,797
At this rate he's not going to make it to the cap
before the ebb tide.

867
01:19:42,840 --> 01:19:45,479
And if he doesn't,
he's going to get swept back out to sea.

868
01:19:45,520 --> 01:19:47,511
- lsn't that being bleak?.
- No, he's right.

869
01:19:47,560 --> 01:19:50,632
BOB: Look, I'll pick up the pace
and he's going to have to keep up.

870
01:19:50,680 --> 01:19:52,636
CHAN: Better do some hypothermia checks.

871
01:19:52,680 --> 01:19:54,398
Can we get closer to him?.

872
01:19:58,520 --> 01:20:01,478
Frank, where are you swimming from?.

873
01:20:02,520 --> 01:20:03,839
England.

874
01:20:03,880 --> 01:20:07,509
- Where in England?.
- Dover.

875
01:20:07,560 --> 01:20:10,438
- What day is it?.
- What?.

876
01:20:10,480 --> 01:20:14,439
- What day is it?.
- Thursday.

877
01:20:14,480 --> 01:20:15,913
He seems all right.

878
01:20:28,520 --> 01:20:30,397
Come on.

879
01:20:30,440 --> 01:20:34,228
I didn't think to ask
where in France he was swimming to.

880
01:20:34,280 --> 01:20:37,716
- There. That's where he's swimming to.
ANGELA: How do you know?.

881
01:20:37,760 --> 01:20:40,069
- Pappy showed me.
- When did Pappy show you?.

882
01:20:40,120 --> 01:20:41,951
I'm not telling you.

883
01:20:46,440 --> 01:20:48,635
BOB: How many times did you try it yourself?.

884
01:20:48,680 --> 01:20:50,079
Three.

885
01:20:50,120 --> 01:20:52,839
- Did you ever make it?.
- Third time lucky.

886
01:21:02,880 --> 01:21:04,871
(Gulls cry)

887
01:21:05,800 --> 01:21:07,836
There it is. Sortie - way out.

888
01:21:28,120 --> 01:21:30,429
- What is it?.
- Ebb tide.

889
01:21:31,880 --> 01:21:35,190
BOB: It's dragging him back out.
EDDlE: What if he can't beat it?.

890
01:21:35,240 --> 01:21:39,358
- Can't you do anything?.
- He's in for the long haul.

891
01:21:39,400 --> 01:21:41,834
- He won't be able to last that long.
- Yes, he will.

892
01:21:41,880 --> 01:21:43,791
CHAN: His body temperature is dropping.

893
01:21:43,840 --> 01:21:46,434
If he doesn't make this beach,
he won't make it at all.

894
01:21:48,080 --> 01:21:49,638
EDDlE: Frank!

895
01:21:49,680 --> 01:21:52,319
You've only three miles to go, Frank.

896
01:21:52,360 --> 01:21:54,999
I know you're hurting,
but you got to swim faster.

897
01:21:55,040 --> 01:21:58,953
The tide's against you.
Frank, you've got to swim faster. Come on!

898
01:22:06,000 --> 01:22:08,116
You can do it, Frank.

899
01:22:08,160 --> 01:22:10,151
You can do it.

900
01:22:19,000 --> 01:22:20,991
(Gulls cry)

901
01:22:35,000 --> 01:22:36,592
(Yells in frustration)

902
01:22:37,200 --> 01:22:41,352
FRANK: Stay there! Stay there! Don't move!
Don't you move from there.

903
01:22:41,400 --> 01:22:42,355
(Whimpering)

904
01:22:50,560 --> 01:22:53,677
Stop that. Stop it!

905
01:22:53,720 --> 01:22:55,711
(Gulls cry)

906
01:22:58,680 --> 01:22:59,556
(Gasps)

907
01:23:07,720 --> 01:23:09,995
Come on, Frank, come on.

908
01:23:44,560 --> 01:23:45,231
No!

909
01:23:46,320 --> 01:23:48,038
Is he all right?.

910
01:23:48,080 --> 01:23:49,399
(Yells)

911
01:23:49,440 --> 01:23:52,557
(Joan cries)

912
01:23:52,600 --> 01:23:54,511
(Yells)

913
01:23:57,000 --> 01:23:58,399
Bloody hell!

914
01:24:16,480 --> 01:24:19,199
I need to come out, lads.

915
01:24:20,680 --> 01:24:22,398
What do you think you're doing?.

916
01:24:22,440 --> 01:24:25,716
Why don't you just take it slower for a wee while,
see if it passes?.

917
01:24:25,760 --> 01:24:27,830
I'm sorry, Chan.

918
01:24:27,880 --> 01:24:29,916
I can't do it, mate.

919
01:24:29,960 --> 01:24:32,315
You're nearly there. Look it's not far.

920
01:24:32,360 --> 01:24:33,554
I can't do it.

921
01:24:33,600 --> 01:24:36,751
OBSERVER: Your body is hurting
because you're burning your fat.

922
01:24:36,800 --> 01:24:38,677
It won't last. You'll get through it.

923
01:24:38,720 --> 01:24:41,712
Yeah, Frank. It's just the pain barrier.
It's all in your mind.

924
01:24:41,760 --> 01:24:45,309
- Get me out! It's too far.
- Bollocks! It's always been this far.

925
01:24:45,360 --> 01:24:49,239
- You come in and swim it, then!
- Fine. Get on board and we all can go home.

926
01:24:49,280 --> 01:24:52,113
All my life I've looked up to you, Frank.

927
01:24:52,160 --> 01:24:53,559
All my life.

928
01:24:53,600 --> 01:24:57,149
- I never saw you back down from anything.
- It's too far.

929
01:24:57,200 --> 01:25:00,158
I'm nobody but you know that.

930
01:25:00,200 --> 01:25:02,873
But I'm not daft. I see what's going on here.

931
01:25:04,240 --> 01:25:06,231
Out here in the middle of nowhere.

932
01:25:09,040 --> 01:25:11,508
But he's not here, is he, Frank?.

933
01:25:12,800 --> 01:25:14,791
He never was.

934
01:25:16,400 --> 01:25:18,789
It's taken you 23 years to find that out.

935
01:25:23,440 --> 01:25:24,839
So what now?.

936
01:25:27,600 --> 01:25:29,591
Well, I'll tell you what now.

937
01:25:30,840 --> 01:25:34,879
You get back to swimming
and you shut up about how far it is.

938
01:25:34,920 --> 01:25:37,229
And you shut up about how much it hurts.

939
01:25:37,280 --> 01:25:39,953
Because you don't have a choice.
You never did.

940
01:25:42,560 --> 01:25:44,676
So, come on.

941
01:25:44,720 --> 01:25:46,915
Get stuck in and put some down.

942
01:25:46,960 --> 01:25:48,951
We're wasting time.

943
01:26:00,320 --> 01:26:02,311
I'll go on, then.

944
01:26:09,760 --> 01:26:10,954
ANGELA: It's him!

945
01:26:11,600 --> 01:26:13,352
No, I can't see for sure but...

946
01:26:13,400 --> 01:26:15,436
- Yeah, that's Frank!
JOAN: Let me see!

947
01:26:35,760 --> 01:26:38,035
Right there. Look. Can you see him?.

948
01:26:42,360 --> 01:26:44,635
Come on. Let's go.

949
01:26:44,680 --> 01:26:46,477
Come on, I need to be there, Mum.

950
01:26:46,520 --> 01:26:48,556
Come on, Mum!

951
01:26:48,600 --> 01:26:49,999
My God!

952
01:28:34,880 --> 01:28:38,668
If he touches him before he gets out of the water
the swim won't be recognised.

953
01:28:38,720 --> 01:28:42,554
- Don't, Rob!
- Don't touch him!

954
01:28:42,600 --> 01:28:43,271
Frank!

955
01:28:45,040 --> 01:28:47,110
Let him get out the water!

956
01:29:06,520 --> 01:29:08,192
What's he want?.

957
01:29:19,320 --> 01:29:21,117
Oh, God!

958
01:29:37,520 --> 01:29:38,748
What?.

959
01:29:40,160 --> 01:29:42,469
Did I miss something?.

960
01:29:45,680 --> 01:29:47,591
- Yes!
- Yes!

961
01:29:50,240 --> 01:29:51,434
Yes!

962
01:29:53,520 --> 01:29:55,511
Come on.

963
01:30:17,200 --> 01:30:19,430
DANNY: We did it! We swam the Channel!

964
01:30:29,080 --> 01:30:30,479
Norman!

965
01:30:31,800 --> 01:30:33,791
I took the ferry.

966
01:30:37,120 --> 01:30:39,714
Get the stone. Get the stone.

967
01:30:39,760 --> 01:30:41,432
Pick up a stone.

968
01:30:41,480 --> 01:30:43,277
Yes!

